OMURAMA DATA WAREHOUSE – SYSTEM SOURCE ANALYSIS INTERVIEW QUESTIONS
    
1. Business Context and Ownership

What is the primary purpose of your system within the business workflow?
Which department or business unit owns and manages this system?
Who are the key stakeholders responsible for data governance and decision-making?
What business processes generate the data captured in your system?
What critical business problems does this system solve?
What data is most valuable for analytics, reporting, and machine learning?
Are there any regulatory, compliance, or privacy requirements associated with your system data?
How frequently is the data required for operational or analytical use?
What is the expected data availability and uptime for integration?
What are the known challenges or limitations with the current data sources?

       2. Architecture and Technology Stack

What type of system are you running (ERP, CRM, custom application, IoT platform, transactional database, etc.)?
What is the underlying database technology (SQL, NoSQL, API-based, streaming, file-based, etc.)?
What programming languages or frameworks were used to build the system?
Is the system hosted on-premise, in the cloud, or hybrid? Specify the environment.
What authentication and authorization mechanisms does the system use?
What is the data storage format (tables, logs, documents, JSON, CSV, Parquet, etc.)?
How is data structured—structured, semi-structured, or unstructured?
What APIs, connectors, or export mechanisms are available for data extraction?
What is the typical system load and performance profile?
Are there event logs, audit logs, or system logs available for ingestion?

          3. Extract and Load (Data Acquisition)

What data needs to be extracted for the bronze layer (tables, logs, files, transactions, events)?
What is the size and growth rate of the data (daily, weekly, monthly volumes)?
How frequently is the data updated (real-time, micro-batch, daily batch)?
What extraction methods are supported (CDC, JDBC/ODBC, APIs, webhooks, file drops, streaming)?
Are there data quality checks already implemented at the source?
What is the expected data latency for ingestion into the data lakehouse?
Are there limits or restrictions on API calls, data exports, or bandwidth?
What security protocols must be followed when extracting data?
What format should the extracted data be delivered in (raw, unchanged, full dumps, incremental)?
Are there any known data anomalies, duplicate issues, or missing values we should plan for?
